    <info>
        <title>Accidentals and Key Signatures</title>
    </info>
    
    <informaltable>
        <thead>
            <tr>
                <th>Musical symbol</th>
                <th>Computer key</th>
            </tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody>
            <tr>
                <td>flat</td>
                <td><cav-computer-key>'</cav-computer-key></td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                <td>sharp</td>
                <td><cav-computer-key>#</cav-computer-key></td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                <td>natural</td>
                <td><cav-computer-key>'#</cav-computer-key> or <cav-computer-key>'#</cav-computer-key></td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                <td>double flat</td>
                <td><cav-computer-key>''</cav-computer-key></td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                <td>double sharp</td>
                <td><cav-computer-key>##</cav-computer-key></td>
            </tr>
        </tbody>
    </informaltable>
    
    <para>To write a key signature you simply type in the sharps/flats successively after a clef. </para>
    
